Purpose
This file defines the common contract every agent must obey.

Linear intent
1. Define `run_result` as one precise shape for every agent output: payload, metrics, and notes.
2. Define the module signature `S` so every agent exposes an `id` and a `run` function.
3. Require `run` to receive the injected runtime services first, because agents now depend on the shared LLM gateway layer.
4. Require `run` to receive the typed context and typed payload after the services.
5. Require `run` to return an `Lwt` promise so agents fit into the asynchronous runtime.
6. Define `packed` so different agent modules can be stored together in the registry.

